====================== README (src/c/core) =======================

This directory contains source files for the basic components of
the PRISM's C part:

  Makefile.gmake ... Makefile for GNU make
  Makefile.nmake ... Makefile for nmake (MSVC++) on Windows
  Makefile.files ... auxiliary Makefile
  bpx.{c,h}           ... utilities for handling Prolog terms
  glue.{c,h}          ... glue code between Prolog and C
  gamma.{c,h}         ... gamma function
  random.{c,h}        ... pseudo random number generator
  idtable.{c,h}       ... ID tables for subgoals and random switches
  idtable_preds.{c,h} ... C interface (wrappers) for accessing ID tables
  termpool.{c,h}      ... hashtable of Prolog terms
  vector.{c,h}        ... utilities for vectors (arrays)
  xmalloc.{c,h}       ... utilities for memory management
  fputil.{c,h}        ... utilities for handling floating point numbers
  stuff.h             ... additional macros and type definitions
  error.{c,h}         ... error handling in the C part

random.c is based on the implementation of Mersenne Twister (http://
www.math.sci.hiroshima-u.ac.jp/~m-mat/MT/emt.html), and gamma.c is
based on the SPECFUN library available in the NETLIB repository
(http://www.netlib.org/).
